</td>
<td align="left" valign="top" rowspan="1" colspan="1">drugs: leflunomide, telithromycin, bosentan, terbinafine, amphotericin b<br>AEs: gamma-glutamyltransferase increased, blood bilirubin increased, liver disorder, aspartate aminotransferase increased, alanine aminotransferase increased, blood alkaline phosphatase increased<br>All of the above drugs have some association with hepatotoxicity, which can cause one or more of the aforementioned adverse events, all of which were characterized as part of the same syndrome.</td>
